        "logLevel": "info",
        "logMessage": "Logging HTTP time result to output",
        "showFieldValues": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "stickyNote1",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -416,
        160
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Credentials Required\n\n### PostgreSQL\nConfigure a **PostgreSQL** credential for the database nodes.\n- Host, port, database, user, password\n- Used by \"Check Table Exists\" and \"Create Table\" nodes\n\n### How It Works\n1. Called by another workflow or manually\n2. HTTP GET to `timeapi.io` for current UTC time\n3. Logs the API response at INFO level\n4. Queries PostgreSQL to check if `workflow_results` table exists\n5. If table exists: logs the HTTP result\n6. If not: creates the table first, then logs the HTTP result\n\nBoth paths converge to log the time result.",
        "color": "yellow",
        "width": 340,
        "height": 370
      }
    }
  ],
